# DATABASE GOVERNANCE — Drizzle + Supabase

## Schema Change Protocol
Before ANY schema change:
1. Check which routers/queries use the affected tables
2. List RLS policies that reference affected tables
3. Write reversible migration
4. Update docs/02_database_schema.md
5. Update drizzle/relations.ts if needed

## Schema Standards
- Every table: id (serial/uuid), createdAt, updatedAt
- Foreign keys: specify ON DELETE (CASCADE, SET NULL, RESTRICT)
- Table prefix: namibia_na_26_ (exception: users)
- Indexes for: FKs, WHERE columns, ORDER BY columns

## Query Standards
- Use Drizzle ORM exclusively in server layer
- Paginate all list queries (.limit() or .range())
- Avoid N+1: use joins/relations
- Specify columns in select, avoid SELECT *

## Migration Standards
- One concern per migration
- Descriptive filenames
- Never modify applied migrations
